On Wed, Aug 28, 2002 at 05:39:34PM +0200, Kontra, Gergely wrote:
> As I can see, the O'Reilly book is available only in pdf format for
> download. This is a portable(?) format, but I think the html version is
> easier to search (grep). Is it possible to put it up in a tgz-d or
> zipped html file(s) for offline users. Or plain text, or windows help

The book is available in HTML shiped in the debian packages
ocaml-book-en and ocaml-book-fr, you can download the packages tarball
from
http://ftp.debian.org/debian/pool/non-free/o/ocaml-book/ocaml-book_1.0-2.tar.gz
and use html version you find inside.

The tarball contains both the english and french versions of the book.

Cheers.

